The Eastern Company’s (SAE) decision is based on a decree issued by the Finance Minister in late February. It comes few days after the parliament passed amendment of some provisions of the value-added tax law.

The mu’assel is a tobacco-based mix that contains molasses, used in smoking hookah.

According to the decision, the new prices of the mu’assel of “Salom & Kas” (500 gram), Abo Negma (500 gram), One for You (250 gram) and Minced Tobacco will be $2, $1.7, $3.1 and $2 respectively.

Eastern Company supplies about 70% of Egypt's cigarette market, according to circulated figures. In August last year, the company decided to raise the cigarette prices by 4.5 to 6%. --EgyptToday--